<article class="page-content">
  <h1>Resources</h1>
  
  <p>This page contains a curated list of resources for learning more about transgender history, supporting the transgender community, and furthering your understanding of transgender experiences. The resources are organized by category for easy navigation.</p>
  
  <section class="resource-section">
    <h2>Books</h2>
    <div class="resource-grid">
      <div class="resource-card">
        <h3>"Transgender History" by Susan Stryker</h3>
        <p>A comprehensive overview of transgender history in the United States, covering major movements, figures, and events from the mid-20th century to the early 2000s.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="resource-card">
        <h3>"Before We Were Trans" by Kit Heyam</h3>
        <p>Explores gender-diverse identities throughout history, challenging modern conceptions of gender and examining how people understood and expressed gender in different cultural contexts.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="resource-card">
        <h3>"Transgender Warriors" by Leslie Feinberg</h3>
        <p>A groundbreaking work that documents the existence of transgender and gender-nonconforming people throughout history and across cultures.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section class="resource-section">
    <h2>Documentaries & Films</h2>
    <div class="resource-grid">
      <div class="resource-card">
        <h3>"Disclosure" (2020)</h3>
        <p>A documentary that explores Hollywood's depiction of transgender people and how those portrayals have influenced American culture and understanding of transgender lives.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="resource-card">
        <h3>"The Death and Life of Marsha P. Johnson" (2017)</h3>
        <p>This documentary examines the life and mysterious death of Marsha P. Johnson, a pioneering transgender activist and a central figure in the Stonewall uprising.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section class="resource-section">
    <h2>Online Resources</h2>
    <div class="resource-grid">
      <div class="resource-card">
        <h3>Digital Transgender Archive</h3>
        <p><a href="https://www.digitaltransgenderarchive.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">digitaltransgenderarchive.net</a></p>
        <p>An online hub for digitized historical materials related to transgender history from dozens of libraries, museums, and archives.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="resource-card">
        <h3>Transgender Archives - University of Victoria</h3>
        <p><a href="https://www.uvic.ca/transgenderarchives/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">uvic.ca/transgenderarchives</a></p>
        <p>Home to the largest trans archives in the world, with materials dating back to the early 20th century.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="resource-card">
        <h3>Transgender Legal Defense & Education Fund</h3>
        <p><a href="https://transgenderlegal.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">transgenderlegal.org</a></p>
        <p>Provides legal resources and support for transgender individuals facing discrimination.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section class="resource-section">
    <h2>Support Organizations</h2>
    <div class="resource-grid">
      <div class="resource-card">
        <h3>The Trevor Project</h3>
        <p><a href="https://www.thetrevorproject.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">thetrevorproject.org</a></p>
        <p>Provides crisis intervention and suicide prevention services to LGBTQ+ youth.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="resource-card">
        <h3>National Center for Transgender Equality</h3>
        <p><a href="https://transequality.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">transequality.org</a></p>
        <p>Advocates for policy changes to advance transgender equality and provides resources for the transgender community.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="resource-card">
        <h3>Trans Lifeline</h3>
        <p><a href="https://translifeline.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">translifeline.org</a></p>
        <p>A trans-led organization that connects trans people to the community, support, and resources they need to survive and thrive.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section class="resource-section">
    <h2>How to Be an Ally</h2>
    <div class="resource-card">
      <ul>
        <li>Educate yourself about transgender issues and terminology</li>
        <li>Use people's correct names and pronouns</li>
        <li>Speak up against transphobia and discrimination</li>
        <li>Support transgender-led organizations and businesses</li>
        <li>Amplify transgender voices and stories</li>
        <li>Respect people's privacy and don't ask invasive questions</li>
        <li>Advocate for inclusive policies in your workplace, school, and community</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section class="resource-section">
    <h2>Contribute to This Project</h2>
    <p>This resource list is by no means exhaustive. If you have suggestions for additional resources or would like to contribute to this project, please <a href="mailto:info@transhistoryproject.org">contact us</a>.</p>
  </section>
</article>
